<AbstractNarration>DMS-0314311&lt;br/&gt;Paul Goerss&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;This award defrays travel costs for younger US-based participants to &lt;br/&gt;attend the Applied Homotopy Theory Program at the University of &lt;br/&gt;Western Ontario in September 2003.  The program will consist of a &lt;br/&gt;one-week workshop for a large range of paricipants and, for the &lt;br/&gt;remainder of the month, a series of mini-courses to be given by &lt;br/&gt;five senior algebraic topologists from the US and Europe.  The support &lt;br/&gt;in this award will be used excusively to support the participation &lt;br/&gt;of US based advanced graduate students, mathematicians in post-doctoral &lt;br/&gt;positions, and a few selected tenure-track mathematicians.  Further &lt;br/&gt;information about the conference may be found at &lt;br/&gt;http://www.math.uwo.ca/homotopy/.</AbstractNarration>
